review_blob: Typical Belgian triple with a hazy golden color and a distinct yeast pattern. Some fruity touches with citrus and banana bit overall it does not rock the boat. Some alcohol sweetness, in balance with a bitter string. Ok triple, as there are many.

Golden with foamy head. Filthy malty nose. Malty body, a long dead silence and then hit by a wave of matured chocolate and old spices. Some spiciness ok, but I am not in a hurry to drink this fire down. This is just out of sync, more, some work needs to be done on this one

Hazy Yellow blond. Initially a metallic touch but thus quickly evolves to a more rounded malty and especially hoppy nose with hints of fruits. First a sense of some alcohol sweetness, but this gives way to a slightly fruity but definitely hoppy taste. Finish is a bit dry, but bitter. Well in balance, does beat expectations...
Dirty light amber. Fruity but malty nose. Taste is round, fruity, slightly peppery, nice smooth to almost creamy, bitter finish. Took me a moment to appreciate. Not too bad
from tap at ZBF 2015. a lot of wood, oak, fruity, banana, dark malts, bitter, alcoholic, chocolate. nice beer.
from tap at ZBF 2015. deep yellow blond, fruity (exotic) nose, full MF, slightly bitter with a sourish touch.
from tap at ZBF 2015. a lot of oak, wood, fruity, chocolate, a lot of punch, bitter sweet chocolate fruity, coffee. complex. very nice beer.
from tap at ZBF 2015. yellow blond color with nose full of apples, fruit. slightly sourish, but finish is in-check. overall fruity, easy going, refreshing. very nice starter.
from tap at ZBF 2015. orange looking color with a very fruity nose, comes back in the taste too. pretty intense, good full MF of exotic fruit, grapefruit. very nice.
from tap at ZBF 2015. blond color with fruity nose and dito taste. bitter, hoppy, ok.
from tap at ZBF 2015. dark brown color with a fruity nose, chocolate. taste: fruity, desert coffee, chocolate, alcohol. very nice, like this!
from tap at ZBF 2015.. amber color, full of spices, peppery but has (to me) a distinct taste of vomit. not my cup of tea.
from tap at ZBF 2015. blond, overdone in the citrus, perfume, spices, basilicum, very wattery. ok to share as a starter ?
at ZBF 2015. ok brew, very young, malty, bit fruity, subtile but the brett is very well hidden. ok, but feels more like it is riding the brett wave than adding to it. expected more.
at ZBF 2015. very smooth body, full of coffee, moccha cream, rich and good MF. very nice
at ZBF 2015. smooth, creamy, malty, hoppy, rich long bitternes. good refresher, great beer.
ZBF 2015. blond color. nose: malt, citrus, spices. smooth, btter with the typical tripel sweet finish. ok beer but that is all.
at ZBF, from tap. 3yrs aged on Wine barrel. nose&taste;: wine liqueur, grapes, fruity, grape juice, bit of a wattery body, lacks punch and body. sweet.
beer_name: Donum Ignis ZOAS (Zuiderbierke Oak Aged Special)

review_blob: Almost clear blond with an off-white head. Nose dominated by a sharp fruity smell, lychee like, bit synthetical. Taste :Soft fluent body, dry and bitter ending. Ok MF. Malty sticky feeling, but hops taking over and a persistent exotic fruity taste is making havoc of the taste experience. Hops, lychee, some sharpness and definitely out of balance. This is still a work in progress...
beer_name: Birrificio dellAspide Jurmanita  Single Hop Palisade

review_blob: Hay yellow, misty with a small off-white head. Delicate hoppy fruity nose, sparkling carbonation. Fruity taste, lemon, Malts subtile in the back. Sweet fruit, but clear bitter ending. Dry. Nice IPA.

From tap@Delirium. Clear yellow white color with a small white head. Nose:malty, sugarish, touch of candy,yeast. Taste: very malty to grainy, sweet, streak of candy, soft and finish is very short lived. Very wattery body, although still 7%..after not tried this for many years... this is a disappointment
Golden color with nose full of tropical fruit. Same is taste, all well balanced, very enjoyable IPA. Long bitter dry finish without going over the edge. Not bad at all....

Dark Orange color with a beige head. Nose is very hoor and forgiven of exotic fruit. Taste is very fruity, with some pine and an overkill of oranges.not bad at all, Ok IPA, bit high on the alcohol % which is pretty much hidden.
beer_name: Weird Beard Holy Hoppin Hell Batch 5

review_blob: Dark brown with a beige head. Nose:Malts, grain, roasted, Malts, hops but very subdued. Taste: bit smoked, beafed up. But again malty with some malt sweetness. Finish is a bit bitter, but short lived. Dry, again some hints of hops but the bigger picture can hardly convince me.

Clear golden color with a white head. Very malty grainy nose and some malt sweetness. Taste : Malts, hop, hop bitterness, very grainy to even grassy. Bit dry, very bitter finish but Overall pretty straight forward. Refreshing. Ok pale ale.
Hazy blond with white head. Yeast malts, ripe fruits. Malt, dry, smooth, sweet body. Below average tripel.

dark golden with an off-white head. nose: malts, yeast, honey, sweet malts, (makes me think of old westmalle tripel). taste: malty, honey, sugarish, fruity twist, but pretty straight forward as a whole. good carbonation, bitter sweet, with the sweet taking over in the end. ok blond, esp. for the 6.5% it is giving..

clear blond with a white head. very malty grainy nose, alcohol and some yeast falling through, straight forward. malty taste, nothing new or earth shocking, but in fact, pretty balanced and even nice. short finish with a sweet body. ok belgian tripel, beats the average.and, very drinkable...

misty golden color with a white head. nose: malts, yeast, spices, unfresh malts, candy, something off here for me (bit of a sharp alcohol sense). sweet sugarish malty taste, with some spices and a spiritzing carbonation that makes me feel drinking "sprite" from the coca cola company. nonetheless, some fruity touches (citrus) to even honey.

misty blond with a white head. nose: yeast, malty, grainy, spices and ok pretty much the same in the taste too. the finish has some initial modest bitterness, but is mainly sweet. very typical belgian, not bad but doesnt rock the boat neither. ok blond
Dry, bit bitter but definitely a sweet fruity ending. Hoppy nose, Malts, fruity with a long finish. Good IPA.

From tap at hoppy loft delirium. Hazy golden color with mediocre white head. Malts, exotic fruit, fruit sweetness, hops, peaches, mango, long stretch, bitter but with a bit of sweetness in the back. Great IPA!
Light yellow with white head. Malt, citrus, yeast, metal in the nose. Malts and yeast, bit hoppy bitterness. Strong carbo. Ok beer

Dark golden, off white head. Malt, bit metal in the nose (not so fresh anymore?). Malt richness, hops, bit dry and bitter. Long finish. Bit of fruits in the back, exotic but limited. Ok IPA, Oct 2015 maturity date... Could be fresher.
Tap at delirium. Golden crystal clear with white head. Yeast, malt, some hops. Spices. Taste:malt, malt sweetness, not so nice hops. Spicy finish (for an IPA). Bitter, sweet ending.

Clear blond with an off-white head. Malts, grain, yeast, citrus, very average. Malt, yeast, some hops. Good carbonation. Bitter, with a sweetish touch in the finish. Ok, for a fortified (?) lager (?).

Brown with a beige head. Nose:yeast, Malts, hops, cherries. Taste:yeast, malt, bit grainy, dark fruits, nuts. Good carbonation. Bitter but with a strong sweet finish that takes over. Long stretch, alcohol is present but not what you would expect for the 13.9%. Overall, in balance. Maybe, undershooting some, would have expected more. Not your daily dram, but definitely good for trying especially with this cold winter weather...
Amber brown color with a beige head. Sweet malts, caramel, liqueur, hints of wood, oak. Dry hops. Finish is ok, but feels I already had better BA than this.
beer_name: Struise XXX Rye Quad Reserva (Bourbon Barrel Aged)

review_blob: Dark brown to almost black color with a brown head. Nose:some roasted malts, coffee, dark chocolate, raisins. Taste: roasted malts, cheap coffee, some metal in the back, bitter and a short finish. Missing some body, good carbonation but still owning a smooth airy. Overall, nice try. Still missing something. Ok beer.
Golden color with an off-white head. Nose: Malts, hops, touch of metal, sugar, hay. Taste: grainy with some malts. Yeast and hop. Good carbonation, lacks depth and punch, one dimensional. Ok beer

Golden blond with an off-white head. Nose: Malts, some alcohol liqueur, spices, frsh bread. Taste : Malts, yeast, distinct metal in the back. Agressive carbonation, sweet finish, but also bit fry. Another Belgian tripel, have had much better...

hay yellow, misty with an airy white head. malts, yeast, spices, bread yeast but still, has something sparkling and refreshing. a lot of yeast in the back, but first you get some malts. pretty straight forward, ok, got some bitter thing with a saltish touch. but this does not make up for the whole. average carbo. okey beer.

hay yellow blond with a hazy off-white head. nose: malts, burned/ashes, yeast, spices, interesting. smoked meat. most of this is coming back in the taste, with grains on the forefront, malts, some belgian hops, smoked meat. light body, bit bitter, very light, average carbo. an atypical blond for sure, good for a starter, especially with BBQ plans. but very specific, likes and dislikes.

bond yellow with a white head. yeast and malts in the nose, bit unfresh. trying to find some citrus. grain. taste: overkill on the citrus, yeast, malts, dry, and wrong footed bitter. dear god, dont call this an IPA. so sorry but way out of sync, too much citrus in the taste. just not nice..

Brown reddish color with a beige head. Malt, some spices, bread yeast, banana. Very straight forward. Taste:some caramel, Malts, yeast. Bit syrup. Above average carbo, sweet finish. Ok Belgian brown, one of the many.

Blond, hazy with a white head. Nose:grain, malt, malt sweetness, white liqueur. Taste: grain, malt, bit of spices in the back. A lot of malt sweetness, fruits, bit of alcohol present. Floral. Smooth carbo, good MF. Bitter sweet finish. Good blond, well balanced with some depth.

Orange looking with an off-white head. Hoppy, floral, fruity nose, intense, makes you want for more. taste is fruity, some hops, but get bit lost in between, some mature malt sweetness. Balanced, but sweet malt finish. Lacks some powder with a reason. Still IPA it is, good what do I love a session.... If only I was on the west coast....

Dark brown color with a beige tiny head. Nose:cherries, wood, vanilla, fruity. Taste:sour, cherries, but also chocolate, wood in the back. Finish:spicy, complex, bit dry, bit fry. Smooth carbo. Alcohol punch in the back. Sour, but not overwhelming. I get some sweet touch in this sour finish. Overall, in my impression the regular was better, but alas, no back to back comparison.
beer_name: Alvinne / Naparbier Gentleman Sour Ale Oak Aged

review_blob: Amber to orange, misty with a tiny head. Sour, with fresh green apples, some wood in the back. Sour finish, but with a distinct sweetish white wine stroke in the back, hint of liqueur as well. Very nice starter...
Hazy blond. Overdose on citrus in nose and taste. Lively carbo. Really? I am paying for this?
